newsitem.title: FRANCE: C. Agricole sees rise in 1996 profits.
newsitem.headline: C. Agricole sees rise in 1996 profits.

text.p: French bank Caisse Nationale de Credit Agricole expects to show a rise in profits in 1996, managing director Lucien Douroux said on Friday.
"Despite the difficult environment, we will have a further rise in our 1996 results after a profit of 6.5 billion francs in 1995," he told a conference.
The bank's profits rose 12.3 percent last year.
